<TITLE> Police arrest JMB activist in Bagmara </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, May 28 (bdnews24.com)  Police Monday arrested a Jamaatul Mujahideen Bangladesh activist in Barobihanali village of Bagmara upazila. Akbar Ali alias Bhanta Akbar also was an accused in a case of aiding the militants, the police said. Bagmara police chief Mirza Golam Sarwar said Akbar was an activist of the banned militant outfit and had been absconding for long. Tipped-off that Akbar had come to meet his family the police raided the place and arrested him. Sarwar said Akbar was the chief of the "hockey stick group" during the 'showdown' of the recently executed JMB kingpin Bangla Bhai in Rajshahi. bdnews24.co
